data.title: I am the Greetest
data.meta_description:
I am the Greetest by Impossible Voyage, released 09 July 2013

Feet are dragging through the water
She is holding my hand
We're all high or drunk or both
But I don't care either way cuz it's our boat and it's our city
And these lights are on for us and this town is built for us
And our collective minds are spinning towards the same goal of union

We were so young, we were so young
still kiss with tongue, but we were so young
We're now alive, we're now alive
Our fathers died, our mothers cried
Had us in mind, Brought us the best, the best of life

It's night out but its bright out and I wanna keep on holding your hand.
So much to learn and never will, utopia would keep us still.
Philip's smart he beat the brain, I wonder if he'll beat us too someday.
But, I'm not gonna wait around to find out, I'll just keep on riding this wave

Dopamine dynasty
Massive velocity
Dopamine dynasty
Equals infinity

I am king, I am glee, fear not, you are with me
Rule the sky, rule the sea, domini, dopamine dynasty
(I'll touch the reset! Don't reset! Touch it now!)

Rule the sky! Rule the sea! Even the gods cannot rule me!
What would I say? How to relay? How are we supposed to live this way?
What the fuck am I supposed to do?

To know the truth is a burden that could break your bones and bury you
To know the truth.

I had my first piece of black berry pie today, and I said my life aint never be the same,
I said my life aint never gonna be the same
